  "extras": {
    "summary": "A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION PROPOSING AMENDMENTS TO SECTIONS 34, 35, 41 AND 42, MISSISSIPPI CONSTITUTION OF 1890, TO PROVIDE THAT A PERSON WHO IS ELECTED AFTER JULY 1, 2026, AND WHO HAS SERVED FOR THREE CONSECUTIVE FOUR-YEAR TERMS IN THE MISSISSIPPI HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OR THE MISSISSIPPI SENATE SHALL NOT BE ELIGIBLE TO SERVE AGAIN IN THAT OFFICE."
  },
